                <fr:title text="Product of matrices">Product of <fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (l\times  m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> be a <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span>. The <html:em><html:strong>product</html:strong></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes  N]]></fr:tex>, is the following <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (l\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span>:</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}_{i\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}},j\in {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}} =
 \bigoplus _{k\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}} N_{k,j}\odot  M_{i,k}
]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                  <fr:contributor>
                    <fr:link href="/marcelofiore/" title="Marcelo Fiore" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/marcelofiore/" display-uri="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
                  </fr:contributor>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J3/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>jms-00J3</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/jms-00J3/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Associativity and unit laws of matrix products">Associativity and unit laws of <fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix products</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The <fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">product</fr:link> of <fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> is associative and has the identity matrix as neutral element.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>For associativity, fix <fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L\in  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (k,l\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (l,m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}\otimes  L = N\otimes {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Below we use the associativity of multiplication, commutativity of addition, and distributivity of multiplication over addition in the semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
    {\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}_{a,d} &=
    \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}_{b,d}\odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    {\mathopen {}\left (
     \bigoplus _{c\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
     N_{c,d}\odot  M_{b,c}
    \right )\mathclose {}}
    \odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    \bigoplus _{c\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    N_{c,d}\odot  M_{b,c}\odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{c\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    N_{c,d}\odot  \bigoplus _{b\in {\mathopen {}\left  [l\right  ]\mathclose {}}} M_{b,c}\odot  L_{a,b}
    \\
    &=
    \bigoplus _{c\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
    N_{c,d}\odot  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}_{a,c}
    \\
    &= {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  L\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{a,d}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>For one unit law, we fix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and recall the definition of the <fr:link href="/jms-00IT/" title="The identity matrix" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IT/" display-uri="jms-00IT" type="local">identity matrix</fr:link> to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes  I^m = M]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  I^m\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} &=
   \bigoplus _{k\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}}
   M_{k, j} \odot  I^m_{i,k}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>Unfolding the definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I^m_{i,j}]]></fr:tex> as given in <fr:link href="/jms-00IT/" title="The identity matrix" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IT/" display-uri="jms-00IT" type="local">Definition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IT/" display-uri="jms-00IT" /></fr:link>, we see that the iterated sum above expands to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m-1]]></fr:tex> copies of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0\odot  M_{k,j}]]></fr:tex> for various <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k \not = i]]></fr:tex> and one copy of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1\odot  M_{i,j}]]></fr:tex>. Thus, we conclude that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\otimes  I^m_{i,j} = M_{i,j}]]></fr:tex> using the absorption and unit laws for multiplication as well as the unit laws for addition in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>The other unit law follows in an analogous way.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
